[[File:A King and a Monk (recto); Text (verso); Folio from an Uttaradhyayanasutra LACMA AC1993.225.1.jpg|thumb|A King and a Monk (recto); Text (verso); Folio from an Uttaradhyayanasutra, LACMA AC1993.225.1]]
{{Jainism}}
'''Uttaradhyayana''' or '''Uttaradhyayana Sutra''' is a [[Śvētāmbara]] text said to be one of the final set lectures given by Lord [[Mahavira]] before his [[Moksha (Jainism)|liberation]].{{sfn|Cort|2001|p=18}} The Uttaradhyayana points to the fact that nudity distinguished Mahavira's monks from those of [[Parshvanatha]] (UttS 23).{{sfn|Dundas|2002|p=47}}

